calculateMyRank().details: This function computes the rank by counting how many players have higher scores. All operations are performed in the encrypted domain: - Uses FHE.gt() to compare encrypted amounts - Uses FHE.select() to conditionally add 1 to the count - Returns encrypted rank that only the caller can decrypt

returns.rankEnc: The encrypted rank (number of players with higher scores + 1)

params._minMineInterval: Minimum time between mines in seconds
params._rewardToken: Address of the reward token contract (can be zero address)

distributeReward(address,uint256).details: This is a simplified reward function. In production, you would: 1. Compute rankings using encrypted comparisons 2. Distribute rewards based on encrypted rankings 3. Use a more sophisticated reward mechanism

params.amount: Amount of reward tokens to distribute
params.player: Address of the player to reward

params.index: The index in the playerAddresses array

returns._0: The player address at the given index
The number of players who have mined
The timestamp of the last mine

params.encryptedAmount: The encrypted amount of resources mined
params.inputProof: The input proof for the encrypted amount

returns._0: Whether the player has mined before

userdoc.notice: A DApp that allows players to mine resources with encrypted amounts. The total mining amount, rankings, and rewards are computed on encrypted data.
